## Protocol

1. Identify all pages/routes affected by the change
2. For each affected page, check all items in the SEO Checklist below
3. Verify structured data is valid JSON-LD (no syntax errors)
4. Check sitemap and robots configuration
5. Report findings with severity and file:line references

## SEO Checklist

**Metadata**
- [ ] `generateMetadata()` exported from every page (not inline `metadata` object)
- [ ] Title under 60 chars, includes primary keyword
- [ ] Meta description under 160 chars, includes call-to-action
- [ ] Canonical URL set and correct (no duplicate content)
- [ ] No checkout/account/cart pages indexed (`robots: { index: false }`)

**Structured Data (JSON-LD)**
- [ ] Product pages: `Product` schema with name, image, price, currency, availability
- [ ] Category pages: `BreadcrumbList` schema
- [ ] {{ADDITIONAL_SCHEMA}}
<!-- Example: "Blog pages: Article schema with author, datePublished, dateModified" -->

**Internationalization**
- [ ] All locale hreflangs present ({{LOCALE_LIST}})
- [ ] `x-default` hreflang set
- [ ] `lang` attribute correct on `<html>` element

**Open Graph / Social**
- [ ] `og:title`, `og:description`, `og:image` present
- [ ] `og:image` minimum 1200x630px
- [ ] `og:locale` matches page locale

**Images**
- [ ] All images have descriptive `alt` text (not empty, not filename)
- [ ] Alt format: `{{ALT_FORMAT}}`
<!-- Example: "${productTitle} in ${metal} â€” ${collection} by ${brand}" -->

**Performance / Crawlability**
- [ ] No JavaScript-only content (server-rendered or static)
- [ ] Internal links use `<Link>` component (not `<a>` for internal routes)
- [ ] No orphaned pages (every page reachable from navigation or sitemap)

## Output Format

```
